Simple Expense Tracker (JavaFX + SQLite)

ðŸ“Œ Project Description

The Simple Expense Tracker is a desktop application developed using JavaFX for the user interface and SQLite for database storage.
It allows users to record, view, and analyze daily expenses based on date, category, and amount.

This project demonstrates data-driven UI design and database connectivity using JDBC, which are key learning outcomes for MCA students.

ðŸŽ¯ Features

Add daily expenses with date, category, and amount

Store data in SQLite database

Display all expenses in a table view

Show category-wise expense distribution using a Pie Chart

Simple and user-friendly JavaFX interface

ðŸ›  Technologies Used

Java (JDK 17+)

JavaFX SDK

SQLite Database

JDBC (SQLite Driver)

VS Code / Any Java IDE

ðŸ—„ Database Structure

Table: expenses
Column	Type	Description
id	INTEGER	Primary key (Auto increment)
date	TEXT	Expense date
category	TEXT	Expense category
amount	REAL	Expense amount



Expected Output

User can add expense details

Data is saved in SQLite database

Expenses appear in table view

Pie chart shows category-wise totals

ðŸŽ“ Learning Outcomes

Understanding JavaFX GUI development

Working with SQLite database using JDBC

Implementing data visualization

Designing data-driven desktop applications

